    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae Trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/237">Heinricus</persName> divina clementia Romanorum <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si circa sanctorum loca
                        beneficia condigna impendimus, hoc nostram imperialem maiestatem condecere
                        credimus, insuper et aeterna premia nos inde adipisci confidimus. Quapropter
                        omnium Christi nostrorumque fidelium universitatem scire volumus, qualiter
                        nos per interventum dilectê nostrê coniugis <persName key="#Queen"
                            ref="#people/365">Agnetis</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops" ref="#people/2129"
                            >Herimanni</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/1850">Coloniensis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> nostri scilicet <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> et Heinrici dilecti
                        cancellarii cêterorumque familiarium nostrorum <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >abbatiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Commutatio #Placitum/iudicatum #Rivers #Fisheries #Saltworks #Wine #Oil #Hay/fodder #Operae #Angaria #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Exemption #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Monasteries #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sanctê Mariê in <placeName
                                ref="#places/4179">Pomposia</placeName></orgName> de antecessore
                        nostro imperatore <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7"
                            >Ottone</persName> a <persName key="#Archbishops" ref="#people/1568"
                            >Frederico</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1471"><placeName ref="#places/594"
                                >Ravennatis </placeName>Ecclesiê</orgName> archiepiscopo iuxta
                        utriusque <rs key="#Placitum/iudicatum">placitum</rs> ad imperialis
                        subiectionem proprietatis <rs key="#Commutatio">concambitam</rs>, ac postea
                        ab <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/130">Heinrico</persName>
                        nostro altero antecessore corroboratam et ab <persName key="#Marquis/duke"
                            ref="#people/3">Ugone</persName> marchione magnifice ditatam et in nos
                        successione imperii et legali iure hereditatam et ad <rs
                            key="Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">nostrê dominationis manus</rs> receptam
                        cum omnibus suis pertinentiis, quicquid videlicet predicta abbatia per
                        aliquod munimen cartarum vel traditionum detinet vel eidem pertinet ab
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/1100">Ecclesia
                            Romana</orgName> et Ravennate aut ab aliqua alia, seu etiam quicquid
                        iure proprietatis detinet aut acquirere in futuro potuerit, id est totam <rs
                            key="#Islands">insulam</rs> integram: a primo latere <placeName
                            ref="#places/4657">Pado</placeName> percurrente in <rs key="#Sea"
                            >mare</rs>, secundo latere <rs key="#Shores">litus maris</rs>, tertio
                        latere <placeName ref="#places/3563">Gauro</placeName>; et <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">piscaria</rs> quê vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fisheries #Ports" ref="#estates/2465"><geogName
                                key="#Fisheries #Ports" ref="#estates/2457"><placeName
                                    key="#Fisheries #Ports">Volana</placeName></geogName></geogName>
                        cum <rs key="#Ports">portu</rs> integro, a <rs key="#Rivers">rivo</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3575">Badarino</placeName> usque in
                        mare, et <rs key="#Massae">massam</rs> quê dicitur <geogName key="#Massae"
                            ref="#estates/2454"><placeName key="#Massae" ref="#places/3559">Lacus
                                Sanctus</placeName></geogName> cum <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscaria</rs> quê vocatur <geogName key="#Fisheries"
                            ref="#estates/2455"><placeName>Tidini</placeName></geogName>, a primo
                        latere <rs key="#Fundi">fundo</rs> qui vocatur <geogName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/3919"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            >Grecolê</placeName></geogName> et fundo qui vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fundi" ref="#estates/2494"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                                ref="#places/3520">Corna Cervina</placeName></geogName> et fluvio
                        qui vocatur <placeName key="#Rivers #Confina" ref="#places/3568"
                            >Cisi</placeName> et <rs key="#Canals">canale</rs> qui vocatur
                            <placeName key="#Canals #Confinia" ref="#places/3569">Curlo</placeName>,
                        a secundo <rs key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">valle</rs> quê vocatur
                            <placeName key="#Confinia #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos" ref="#places/4681"
                            >Farullê</placeName> et fluvio qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Confinia" ref="#places/3564">Conca Agathê</placeName>
                        descendente in Gaurum, a tertio latere ipso Gauro, a quarto vero Pado
                        percurrente; insuper <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> unam integram quê vocatur
                            <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/2487"><placeName key="#Curtes"
                                ref="#places/4619">Hustolatus</placeName></geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Plebs">plebe</rs> sua et aliam quê vocatur <geogName key="#Curtes"
                            ref="#estates/3920"><placeName key="#Curtes" ref="#places/4695"
                                >Baoria</placeName></geogName> et curtem aliam quê vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/3921"><placeName key="#Curtes">Ultra
                                canale</placeName></geogName>, cum omnibus ad monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1474">Sanctê Mariê in
                            Xenodochio</orgName> pertinentibus et cum omnibus quê predictê abbatiê
                        Ugo marchio filius <persName><name ref="Hubertus">Uberti</name></persName>
                        dedit, quicquid etiam habet aut acquirere potest infra Padum et <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4646">Attesin</placeName> fluvium vel infra
                        Padum et <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3588">Sandalum</placeName> et
                        quantacumque in apostolicê sedis privilegio releguntur, verum etiam queque
                        habet aut acquirere potest in civitate Ravenna et infra totum <rs
                            key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/485"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2449">Comacliensem</geogName></placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3538"><geogName
                                key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2435"
                            >Gavellensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/80"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/84"
                                >Ferrariensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/7"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2439"
                                >Bononiensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/38"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/208"
                                >Mutinensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3512"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2409"
                                >Corneliensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3513"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2458"
                                >Faventinum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3515"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2459"
                                >Liviensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/4602"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2480"
                                >Pupiliensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/1890"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1479"
                                >Cesenatem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                                ><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1478"
                                >Monteferetranum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1806"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1480">Ariminensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1807"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2482">Pensauriensem</geogName></placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1808"><geogName
                                key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2481">Fanensem</geogName></placeName>
                        et <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1812"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2371">Urbinatem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1803"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1481">Castellanum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/2752"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2462">Perusinum</geogName></placeName> et in omnibus
                        quoque locis, cum areis, edificiis, <rs key="#Castle">castris</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Churches">capellis</rs>, <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>,
                            <rs>salictis</rs>, <rs key="#Oil">olivetis</rs>, <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs> , <rs>planitiebus</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Rivers">aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscationibus</rs>, <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >venationibus</rs> , <rs key="#Saltworks">salinis</rs> et cum omni
                        utilitate quê vel nominari vel scribi possit, <rs key="#Exemption">ab omni
                            subiectione archiepiscoporum excutimus</rs>, ut regalis in perpetuum sit
                        nullis dominantium personis subiecta. Sint <rs key="#Monks">monachi</rs>
                        eius ab omni secularis <rs key="#Operae">servitii</rs> infestatione securi
                        et ab omni <rs key="#Angaria">angaria</rs> cum suis hominibus remoti; qui de
                        suis qualem voluerint abbatem eligant ab episcopo <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1498">Comacliensi</orgName> consecrandum, qui,
                        si sibi pro pecunia vel aliqua humana potestate molestus esse voluerit,
                        veniat ad archiepiscopum Ravennatem ab eo benedicendus, et si hoc in isto
                        quod in primo invenerit, ad qualemcumque episcopum voluerit causa
                        consecrationis properet. Si quis autem hoc preceptum fregerit, componat <rs
                            key="#Penalty">ducentas libras auri cocti</rs>, medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camerê nostrê</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem prelibato
                            monasterio</rs>. Quod ut verius credatur, hanc imperialem paginam manu
                        propria roboratam sigillari iussimus. Signum domni Heinrici secundi
                        Romanorum invictissimi imperatoris augusti. Heinricus cancellarius vice
                        Herimanni archicancellarii recognovi. Data V id. apr. anno dominicae
                        incarnationis MXLVII, indictione XV, anno autem domni Heinrici tercii
                        ordinationis eius XVIII, regnantis quidem VIII, secundi imperantis primo.
                        Actum Ravenne; in Dei nomine feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
